Year = {1981},
Volume = {46},
Number = {2},
Pages = {136-139},
Abstract = {Observations made in late October, 1979, indicate that the wasp,
   Polistes fuscatus, and the locust borer, Megacyllene robiniae, are
   selective pollinators of goldenrod (Solidago canadensis). The
   pollination system is probably complicated, involving mimicry between
   these (and perhaps other) insects and possible specialized roles in
   cross-versus self-pollination. A differential pollination of the fall
   weed flora (e.g., Solidago canadensis vs. Aster spp.) was evident, and
   is deserving of further investigation.},
